    • bodyPart

      public static BodyPart bodyPart​(byte[] rawBytes, String name, String fileName)
      Defines a part of a request body as an array of bytes. By default it sets Content-Type to application/octet-stream. It is possible to change content type to another by invocation of setContentType(String)
      Parameters:
      rawBytes - is byte array content
      name - is a name of a part
      fileName - is filename of a part
      Returns:
      an instance of BodyPart

    • bodyPart

      public static BodyPart bodyPart​(File file, String name, String fileName, boolean calculateContentType)
      Defines a part of a request body as a file.
      Parameters:
      file - is a file content
      name - is a name of a part
      fileName - is filename of a part
      calculateContentType - enables calculation of content type. It sets Content-Type to application/octet-stream when calculateContentType is false or it is not possible to get mime. It is possible to change content type to another by invocation of setContentType(String)
      Returns:
      an instance of BodyPart

    • bodyPart

      public static BodyPart bodyPart​(File file, String name, boolean setFileName, boolean calculateContentType)
      Defines a part of a request body as a file.
      Parameters:
      file - is a file content
      name - is a name of a part
      setFileName - defines to set filename to the name of the given file (File.getName()) or keep it empty.
      calculateContentType - enables calculation of content type. It sets Content-Type to application/octet-stream when calculateContentType is false or it is not possible to get mime. It is possible to change content type to another by invocation of setContentType(String)
      Returns:
      an instance of BodyPart
